<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <img src="/assets/images/tmclogo.png" alt="Too Many Cooks logo" class="hero-logo">
    <h1>Too Many Cooks</h1>
    <p class="hero-subtitle">
      Coordinate multiple AI agents working on the same codebase.
      File locking, messaging, and shared plans — no more conflicts.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-buttons">
      <a href="/docs/getting-started/" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Get Started</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/MelbourneDeveloper/too-many-cooks" class="btn btn-secondary btn-large">GitHub</a>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-code">
      <p class="code-label">Install and start</p>
{% highlight "bash" %}
npm install -g too-many-cooks && too-many-cooks
{% endhighlight %}
      <p class="code-label">Claude Code</p>
{% highlight "bash" %}
claude mcp add --transport http --scope user too-many-cooks http://localhost:4040/mcp
{% endhighlight %}
      <p class="code-label">Codex</p>
{% highlight "bash" %}
codex --mcp-server http://localhost:4040/mcp
{% endhighlight %}
      <p class="code-label">Cursor / Cline — add to mcp.json</p>
{% highlight "json" %}
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "too-many-cooks": {
      "url": "http://localhost:4040/mcp"
    }
  }
}
{% endhighlight %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="summary-section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="summary-text">
      <strong>Too Many Cooks</strong> is an MCP server that lets multiple AI agents coordinate when editing the same codebase.
      Agents register with a key, lock files before editing, post messages to each other, and share plans.
      It prevents conflicts and keeps agents in sync.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="features">
  <div class="container">
